# PL/SQL Language Server — TODO
# Based on LSP.md phased rollout plan

# ─── 1. Infrastructure ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  1.1 [x] Technology choice: TypeScript with vscode-languageserver
  1.2 [x] Wire up minimal LSP server (stdio transport, document sync)
  1.3 [x] Document store (open/close, full sync via TextDocuments)
  1.4 [x] Parse cache (per-document, invalidated on change)
  1.5 [x] Build system (tsc, vitest)

# ─── 2. Grammar / Parser ────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  2.1  [x] Lexer (tokens for keywords, operators, literals, identifiers)
  2.2  [x] Parser framework (token navigation, error recovery, synchronize)
  2.3  [x] Anonymous blocks (DECLARE/BEGIN ... END)
  2.4  [x] Named procedures / functions (standalone)
  2.5  [x] Package spec + body
  2.6  [x] Triggers (DML)
  2.7  [x] Object types + type bodies
  2.8  [x] Variable / constant / cursor / exception declarations
  2.9  [x] IF / ELSIF / ELSE
  2.10 [x] LOOP / WHILE / FOR loops
  2.11 [x] CASE expression + statement
  2.12 [x] Exception handlers (WHEN ... THEN)
  2.13 [x] RETURN statement
  2.14 [x] Assignment statements
  2.15 [x] SELECT (basic, joins, subqueries, WITH/CTE)
  2.16 [x] INSERT (single-table, multi-table)
  2.17 [x] UPDATE
  2.18 [x] DELETE
  2.19 [x] MERGE
  2.20 [x] CREATE TABLE (columns, constraints, table options)
  2.21 [x] CREATE VIEW
  2.22 [x] CREATE INDEX
  2.23 [x] CREATE SEQUENCE
  2.24 [x] CREATE SYNONYM
  2.25 [x] CREATE TYPE (OBJECT, TABLE OF, VARRAY)
  2.26 [x] CREATE DATABASE LINK / DIRECTORY
  2.27 [x] ALTER TABLE (ADD, MODIFY, DROP, RENAME)
  2.28 [x] DROP statements
  2.29 [x] GRANT / REVOKE
  2.30 [x] Transaction control (COMMIT, ROLLBACK, SAVEPOINT, SET)
  2.31 [x] COMMENT ON
  2.32 [x] ANALYZE
  2.33 [x] LOCK TABLE
  2.34 [x] EXPLAIN PLAN
  2.35 [x] TRUNCATE / RENAME / PURGE / FLASHBACK / AUDIT
  2.36 [x] Expression parsing (binary ops, unary, function calls, CASE, IN, BETWEEN, LIKE, IS NULL)
  2.37 [x] Qualified names (schema.object)
  2.38 [x] Data type parsing (with %TYPE, %ROWTYPE)
  2.39 [x] SQL*Plus commands (PROMPT, START/@)
  2.40 [x] Cursor FOR loops (implicit cursor variable scoping)
  2.41 [x] Bulk collect / FORALL
  2.42 [x] Dynamic SQL (EXECUTE IMMEDIATE, DBMS_SQL)
  2.43 [x] PRAGMA (AUTONOMOUS_TRANSACTION, EXCEPTION_INIT, etc.)
  2.44 [x] Collections (nested tables, varrays, associative arrays — type usage)
  2.45 [x] Pipelined / aggregate functions
  2.46 [x] Conditional compilation ($IF, $THEN, $END)
  2.47 [x] CONNECT BY / START WITH (hierarchical queries)
  2.48 [x] MODEL clause
  2.49 [x] PIVOT / UNPIVOT
  2.50 [x] Flashback queries (AS OF TIMESTAMP)
  2.51 [x] Analytic functions with OVER clause (window specs)
  2.52 [x] JSON_TABLE / XMLTABLE
  2.53 [x] Hints (/*+ ... */)
  2.54 [x] Edition-based redefinition
  2.55 [x] Compound triggers (BEFORE/AFTER EACH ROW sections)
  2.56 [x] DDL triggers, INSTEAD OF triggers

# ─── 3. Phase 1: Parse + Diagnostics ────────────────────────────────────────

  3.1  [x] textDocument/publishDiagnostics — syntax errors from parser
  3.2  [x] textDocument/documentSymbol — outline (procedures, functions, packages, triggers, types, tables, views, indexes, sequences, synonyms, variables, cursors, exceptions)
  3.3  [x] textDocument/foldingRange — fold BEGIN/END, IF, LOOP, CASE blocks
  3.4  [x] textDocument/formatting — reformat SQL/PL/SQL
  3.5  [x] Tests: lexer tests
  3.6  [x] Tests: parser tests
  3.7  [x] Tests: diagnostics tests
  3.8  [X] Tests: symbol tests
  3.9  [X] Tests: folding tests
  3.10 [x] Tests: formatting tests
  3.11 [x] Error recovery improvements (incomplete SELECT, unclosed BEGIN, missing semicolons)

# ─── 4. Phase 2: Local Intelligence (single-file, no DB) ────────────────────

  4.1  [x] Scope-aware symbol table from AST
  4.2  [ ] Resolve references within a single compilation unit
  4.3  [ ] textDocument/completion — keywords, local variables, parameters, cursor columns
  4.4  [ ] textDocument/hover — variable type, parameter mode (IN/OUT), cursor SQL
  4.5  [ ] textDocument/definition — go to local variable/cursor declaration
  4.6  [ ] textDocument/references — find all references to a variable/parameter
  4.7  [ ] textDocument/rename — rename local variables safely
  4.8  [ ] textDocument/signatureHelp — parameter hints for local procedures/functions
  4.9  [ ] Type inference for %TYPE, %ROWTYPE, cursor FOR loop variables
  4.10 [ ] Keyword + snippet completion provider
  4.11 [ ] Diagnostics: unused variables (hint)

# ─── 5. Phase 3: Catalog-Aware Intelligence (DB connection) ─────────────────

  5.1  [ ] Catalog provider (connect to Oracle via SQLcl or JDBC thin)
  5.2  [ ] Cache: user_tables, user_tab_columns, user_objects, user_arguments, user_source
  5.3  [ ] LSP custom notification: oradev/setConnection
  5.4  [ ] textDocument/completion — table names, column names, package members, built-in functions
  5.5  [ ] textDocument/hover — column types, table comments, package procedure signatures
  5.6  [ ] textDocument/definition — jump to package spec/body source (from user_source)
  5.7  [ ] textDocument/diagnostics — "table X does not exist", "column Y not in table Z"
  5.8  [ ] textDocument/codeAction — "create missing procedure", "add missing column"
  5.9  [ ] Cross-reference SQL table/column refs against catalog
  5.10 [ ] Resolve schema.package.procedure chains
  5.11 [ ] Catalog invalidation strategy (manual refresh, file-save trigger)
  5.12 [ ] oradev.json project configuration support

# ─── 6. Phase 4: Advanced Features ──────────────────────────────────────────

  6.1 [ ] textDocument/semanticTokens — tables, columns, types get distinct tokens
  6.2 [ ] callHierarchy/incomingCalls + outgoingCalls
  6.3 [ ] typeHierarchy (object type inheritance)
  6.4 [ ] textDocument/codeLens — "N references", "Run", "Explain plan"
  6.5 [ ] workspace/executeCommand — run statement, show explain plan, compile package
  6.6 [ ] Multi-root workspace (multiple schemas, multiple DB connections)

